OL,3,C'Everything is worse': MS stem cell
OL,4,Ctreatment leaves man with side effects
OL,6,FA dad from Surrey who has undergone a
OL,7,Fpioneering stem cell transplant to try
OL,8,Fhalt the progression of his MS, says
OL,9,Fhe's devastated things have not
OL,10,Fimproved.
OL,12,FMartin Stokes undertook a radical
OL,13,Fprocedure that involved aggressive
OL,14,Fchemotherapy that wiped out his immune
OL,15,Fsystem and required four months in
OL,16,Fisolation - away from his wife and
OL,17,Fyoung daughter.
OL,19,FBut six months after the treatment,
OL,20,FMartin says it has made his symptoms
OL,21,Fworse.
